# Concepts to learn Unity  

See how's it's done and learn by yourself ! 
**5-10 minutes exercices and examples to be comfortable with Unity development.**

> [!NOTE]
> This tutorial was built using **Unity 6.3** and the **"3D (Built-In Render Pipeline)" template**.

> [!TIP]
> Feel free to jump arround the different topics as you wish.
> Each topic can be aborded standalone.  

| Number | Name | Topic |
| - | - | - |
| **1** | **Editor UI** | Familiarize yourself with the editor's UI |
| **2** | **Physics** | Familiarize yourself with the built-in physics |
| **3** | **Components** | Use components on your game objects |
| **4** | **Managers** | Creating a Manager game object to manager your objects |
| **5** | **Assets** | Import and use different kinds of assets |
| **6** | **Prefabs and Scenes** | Be more efficient by leveraging unity's tools |
| **7** | **Lightning** | Add lightning to your scenes |
| **8** | **In-Game UIs** | Learn In-Game UIs |
| **9** | **Nav Mesh** | Use Unity's built-in path finding feature |  